caption: Great food! Friendly staff! Our waitress was awesome! Very cool atmosphere. We are from Ohio and was in DC for Prayer March 2020. We searched for places within walking distance from our hotel and picked the place at random. Had no clue what to expect, glad we chose Stan's. Will definitely go again if we ever make it back to DC

I came into DC at 3:30am yesterday when I was supposed to land at 8pm the night before. The storm had made things very... tumultuous. I luckily stumbled upon Chopt on my morning walk around 11am. Everyone here was super friendly despite my disoriented state. I could see all the ingredients were beautifully fresh and everything appeared clean.  I think I asked the cashier to repeat himself 4 times and he patiently did each time, with a kind smile as he attempted to offer me bread. Thanks for meeting me where I was! My body proceeded to walk 10 miles that day (yesterday) and another 15 today. I will return within this trip to have some food before I fly back out!

Ready for healthy whole food?  Chopt is the go-to place for healthy and delicious.  Fantastic service with friendly and helpful responses to questions and special requests.  Features local grown produce, farm to table with the list on the wall.  The menu and ingredients have lots of healthy variety, so I could eat here every day.  Grateful to have found Chopt on my visit to Washington DC.

I've been to Chopt twice (same location) and both times were disappointing.    The staff don't seem to know what ingredients belong in which salads, nor do the check to ensure all ingredients are there.  I pointed out three times to three different people that my salad was missing cabbage, jicama and cilantro.  The manager finally believed me and gave me a large side of cabbage, no cilantro, and about a teaspoon of jicama.  A $12 salad missing half of the ingredients. Not impressed and won't be returning. Will be frequenting to SwetGreen instead.
Grabbed a bite before visiting the white house.  Good wraps and salads.  Gets really busy on weekdays from noon for the lunch crowd.

Absolutely delicious and super convenient. There is a long line at lunch time, but I always order online and get to skip the lines and go straight to the pick-up area. Even with the lines, they are pretty fast and very friendly. Definitely recommend!

The people who work here are truly some of the friendliest and warmest people that I have encountered during my years here in DC. They all make an effort to get to know you while you’re in line and are extremely knowledgeable of their food. The managers take the time to work on the little details, whether cleaning off the glass doors, or the tables in the restaurant and this work ethic shows time after time. I love the salads that they offer and the people make the experience so personal. I have made a connection here and I feel extremely valued as a customer every time I step foot in the door. Without a doubt you should stop in and try it sometime! Personal recommendation: Mexican Caesar, it’s awesome!

Everyone knows you can get a great salad at Chop't but I wanted to highlight the excellence in customer service at the 1730 PA Ave location. The manager, Walter, can always be found making sure the lines are moving quickly- greeting frequent guests in a friendly manner, and addressing concerns when any issues arise. I have noticed that while other locations try to cut corners by reusing cutting boards and tools, this location is great about using clean items each time. This is especially important for those of us with allergies which Walter and his staff are well informed of. I would highly recommend frequently this location and appreciate all of Walter's efforts - he certainly sets the bar high for the city lunch experience!
